<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-03T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="340" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d340">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1503.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Commissioner <persName type="from">Fort</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi>
                                </placeName> [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1914-09-03T16:00:00-05:00" notBefore="1914-08-31T00:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date><hi rend="italic">; received September
                                    3, 1914, 4 p.m.]</hi>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Yesterday we took up the Arias situation with Provisional President. He
                            asked that he be granted a few days to handle it himself. Today he
                            advised he had word from Arias agreeing to acknowledge his authority and
                            to disband at once. Everything is getting so much better here advise
                            letting Provisional President handle it at present. Commission is in
                            daily touch with situation. We get many inaccurate reports from those
                            who send them from various motives. Arias can be gotten much more surely
                            and easily after Báez arranges than now. Advise awaiting action by Báez,
                            we keeping in touch with situation. President Báez swore in his Cabinet
                            today and presented them to us.</p>
                        <p>Tomorrow we get committee of Cabinet to discuss election plans.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Fort</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>